{"id": "duc04-testb-16:15#46", "contents": "The endorsement of Schumer is largely attributed to the Monica Lewinsky scandal, which has led Democrats to fear that the Republicans will gain a filibuster-proof majority in the Senate. Labor leaders like Rivera fear that a strong Republican majority would push through anti-union legislation, such as proposals to curb labor's political spending and cut financing for the National Labor Relations Board. Rivera emphasized that the decision was not personal but based on national considerations, citing the leadership of the Republican Party as being \"far more conservative, far more anti-labor, far more anti-worker, far more pro-business.\""}
